generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 4802 feet, Mount Moosilauke is a standout peak in New Hampshire. Known for its approachable and scenic terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Gorge Brook Loop**, a **10.0 mile** route gaining **3288 feet** of elevation. As part of the **NH48 4000-Footers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **South Kinsman**, which is just 8.2 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.
